  "body": "#### System information\r\n$ geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.6.7-stable\r\nGit Commit: ab5646c532292b51e319f290afccf6a44f874372\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.7.4\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.7\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nstart one instance of geth with explicit --datadir\r\nstart another instance geth and specify the ipc file path (and|or the --datadir)\r\ngeth attaches successfully\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\ngeth uses the default ipc path, and fails to connect\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```\r\nme@geth-test:~$ \r\nme@geth-test:~$ ls /home/me/data/geth.ipc \r\n/home/me/data/geth.ipc\r\nme@geth-test:~$ geth --ipcpath /home/me/data/geth.ipc  attach\r\nFatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial unix /home/me/.ethereum/geth.ipc: connect: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n ",
